5 Uses of Face/Object Detection
Face Unlock in Smartphones
Detects and recognizes a user’s face for secure authentication.
Surveillance Systems
Identifies suspicious activities or unknown individuals in public areas.
Automatic Attendance System
Uses face detection to mark attendance in classrooms or offices.
Self-Driving Cars
Detects objects like pedestrians, vehicles, and traffic signals.
Retail Analytics
Tracks customer movement and behavior in stores for business insights.
Designed Solution: Smart Attendance System
Problem:

Manual attendance is time-consuming and prone to errors or proxy attendance.

Solution:

Develop a Face Detection-based Attendance System that automatically marks attendance when a student enters the classroom.

Working:
A camera captures live video
Face detection algorithm identifies students
Recognized faces are matched with stored data
Attendance is automatically recorded in a database
Benefits:
Saves time
Prevents proxy attendance
Improves accuracy